<subSubSection pageId="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1155,1381,1511]" box="[160,285,1381,1407]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="5">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1155,1381,1511]" pageId="5">
The specific name is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[721,786,1417,1442]" italics="true" pageId="5">grand</emphasis>
- = large, and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1049,1140,1417,1442]" italics="true" pageId="5">spinatus</emphasis>
= spinous, in reference to the dorsal base of valva with a large spine-like projection in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
